SIMPLE: intellective
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intellective
<hw>In`tel*lec"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>intellectif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or produced by, the intellect or
understanding; intellectual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having power to understand, know, or comprehend;
intelligent; rational.</def> <rj><au>Glanvill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Capable of being perceived by the understanding
only, not by the senses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Intellective</qex> abstractions of logic and metaphysics.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intellectively</ent>⟦br⟧
